matrix or data.frame to tibble (taken from tidyquant)

Source: R/utilities.R
matrix_to_tibble.Rd

matrix or data.frame to tibble (taken from tidyquant)

matrix_to_tibble(x, preserve_row_names = "row.names", ...)

Arguments

x

a matrix
preserve_row_names

give name to rownames column, if NULL discard rownames
...

further parameters passed to as_tibble

See also

Other utilities: INTERNAL_FUNCTIONS_BY_FAMILY, get_UniprotID_from_fasta_header(), jackknifeMatrix(), multigroupVolcano(), my_jackknife(), pairs_smooth(), pairs_w_abline(), panel.cor(), panel.hist(), removeNArows(), split2table(), table_facade.list(), table_facade()

Examples

x <- matrix(rnorm(20), ncol=4)
rownames(x) <- LETTERS[1:nrow(x)]
matrix_to_tibble(x)

#> Warning: The `x` argument of `as_tibble.matrix()` must have unique column names if `.name_repair` is omitted as of tibble 2.0.0.
